FBIS4-4596 "dreas064_c_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-064 Daily Report 3 Apr 1994 North Korea U.S. Defense Secretary Perry's Remarks Reported U.S. Defense Secretary Perry's Remarks Reported ROK Opposition Leader Comments SK0304090294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0806 GMT 3 Apr 94 SK0304090294 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- Yi Ki-taek, president of the South Korean opposition Democratic Party, in a statement April 1 denounced a reckless war blast of U.S. Secretary of Defense William Perry, according to a radio report from Seoul. Crying about fictitious "development of nuclear weapons" by North Korea, the U.S. secretary of Defense said they were ready for a war to check it. Yi condemned this as a blast designed to heighten the crisis on the Korean peninsula.
